{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_133","type":"agent_message","text":"I’ve isolated one likely metadata bug: the `IndyInterface` reflection entry is conditioned on `groovy.lang.GroovySystem`, but `IndyInterface` needs its own reflective method-handle lookup before `GroovySystem` is reached. I’m tightening those conditions now and dropping the ineffective `--add-opens` tweak so the fix stays metadata-scoped."}}
